 a teacher’s perspective how teacher professionalism may be conceptualized, this book critiques dominant global narratives and conceptions based on deficit discourses. The authors argue that a decolonial lens can help to contextualize the perspectives, experiences and material conditions of teachers in the global South, and the value of such a framework for informing global debates and decision-making in education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aDecolonization. 0aTeachersxTraining ofzSouthern Hemisphere. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Colonialism & Post-Colonialism.2bisacsh1 aAviles Nunez, Nidia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBarrett , Angeline, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBernal, Alexandra, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCameron, Leanne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aColes, Alf, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCrossley, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJuma, Zawadi, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMitchell, Rafael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMitchell, Rafael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaulson, Julia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aReda, Nigusse Weldemariam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRowsell, Jennifer, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTusiime, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVejarano, Beatriz, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWeldemariam Reda, Nigusse, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781529242